The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, has confirmed 1,588 new cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) in 19 states and the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja. The development brings the total number of confirmed COVID-19 infections in the country to 139,242. NCDC made the announcement Saturday night while giving the usual daily report on its Twitter handle. The public health agency also confirmed 6 fatalities, bringing the total number of COVID-19 related deaths in the country to 1,647. The report reads: 1,588 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-535 Anambra-218 Oyo-155 FCT-150 Kano-124 Gombe-60 Kaduna-49 Ebonyi-48 Plateau 46 Akwa Ibom-39 Niger-37 Edo-33 Katsina-23 Rivers-18 Taraba-15 Nasarawa-14 Ogun-11 Delta-9 Ekiti-2 Jigawa-2 139,242 confirmed 112,557 discharged 1,647 deaths.‚Äù